 2. Transformers

	—> INTRODUCED IN 2017 > used for language translation by GOOGLE
	—> now : A Deep neural network architecture
	—> input text -> preprocessing (tokenisation) -> Encoding (Vector AND Positional Embedding)-> partial output -> Decoding -> Output
	—> GPT doesn’t have encoder, only decoder

	—> SELF ATTENTION MECHANISM : a dynamic mechanism that calculates context-dependent relationships between words within the same sequence (e.g The ‘cat’ was ill so ‘it’ couldn’t cross the street.)

BERT VS GPT  (both use transformers)
-> Bidirectional Encoder Representations from transformers
-> BERT looks a the sentence from both the left and the right side
-> it is really good for sentiment analysis.
-> BERT can differentiate between the river bank and the financial bank.
-> can predict hidden words in between sentences

WHEREAS

-> GPT only reads the sentences from left to right.
-> not really food at sentiment analysis
->can only predict the word at the end of the sentence

—> Not all transformers are LLMs and vice versa
—> Transformers are also used in CNNs (Vision Transformers) 
